p: \r\pn, am I ever glad to see you.
\rI heard about what happened with Damian down in Audrey's base.
\rListen... I don't know what's going on with him.
\rBut we're going to find a way to help him, okay? I promise.
\rI'm happy you're here. I was worried I'd have to fight the Infernal Cult by myself.
\b-and as it turns out, everyone was interpreting the prophecy wrong!
\bWhat do you mean? Did you find out what it was really trying to say?
\bThat hero? They'll defeat all the other cults, save the region, yadda yadda yadda.\nThen, not only will they not defeat us, they'll end up joining us.
\bThat's... wonderful.\nAnd since the only candidates for the hero are that Rain-team Leader or one of those kids, I don't think they're going to be joining us willingly.
\bExactly. Which means our gift is more powerful than we first thought.
\rWhat on earth is wrong with you?
\rYou were with us at the library when we heard that prophecy!
\rYou were supposed to be on our side!\nYou told us how important that prophecy was- special information that nobody else knows!
\rAnd now... you're just sharing it to Zenith and Infernal!
\rYou betrayed us! We don't have our advantage anymore!
\bYour advantage was gone long before that.
\bZenith knew about the prophecy the moment you did, you foolish girl.
\bYou never did ask my name.\nYou really should have. Names are important. They have power.
\bThe chance of hearing that prophecy is the only reason I ever worked at that library at all.\nHaving to wear hair dye was annoying enough...
\bWhen the three of you showed up and that oracle finally appeared...
\bEvery tiresome moment there became worthwile when I finally heard him predict our victory.
\bWe don't fear children, or any kind of prophecy.
\bOne of you will join us. It is foretold.
\bYou act like you have a choice.
\bBut so be it. If you want a fight, then that's what you'll get.
\bSo, \pn, Nora. Come at us. Show us what you can do!
\bHmph. Not bad.\nI'm kind of hoping it'll be you who ends up joining us.
\bI'm going to show you exactly what we're capable of.
\bRise! Show yourself to your loyal servants!
\rWhat? How... how did Groudon join you so easily?
\rYou didn't even catch it! What's going on?!
\bYou didn't come down here expecting us to catch Groudon, did you?
\bYou clearly haven't done your research on us before you came.
\bWe were the first. It's only natural that we caught the legendary we worshipped long ago.
\bWe're merely waking Groudon from its rest.\nAfter all, it's nearly time to begin.
\bWe're in the mountains if you're still aching for a fight.\nI'll be waiting.
\rI... I didn't know they've already caught Groudon...
\rYou saw how quickly the Abyssal Cult moved into action after they caught Lugia.\nI don't know what Infernal is planning, but I don't like it.
\rI'm going to head back to the library.
\rSomething Zenith said made me think about Perfection.
\rIt's a long shot, but I have an idea.\nI need to research this more.
\r\pn, you should probably head to Selene City, there's a Gym there, after all.\nI'll see you around.
